               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> <pos expand="abstractum, -e">abstr.</pos> </gramGrp>: <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> cantus Halleluja </quote></cit>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">አንቀጸ፡ ሃሌታ፡</foreign> (v. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሃሊታ፡</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">እምዮሐንስ፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> tabula Hallelujarum inde a Joannis festo </quote></cit>, <ref cRef="Deg." loc="">Deg. </ref> (<lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl> <ref cRef="Catal. Cod. Aeth. Mus. Brit." loc="37">Catal. Cod. Aeth. Mus. Brit. p. 37</ref>). </sense>
               
            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"><cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>hālletā</quote></cit> <sense n="G" xml:id="TG"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሃሌታ፡</foreign> recueil des divers modes de chant des alléluia pour l’année liturgique (temporal et sanctoral, «de Jean à Jean»). <lb/>
 C’est ici la particule enclitique <foreign xml:lang="gez">ታ፡</foreign> de sens collectif, ajoutée à la première partie du mot alléluia (souvent écrit <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡</foreign>), qui donne à ce vocable liturgique <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሃሌታ፡</foreign> le sens de recueil. Voir infra <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡</foreign> et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላምታ፡</foreign>. <lb/>
 <bibl><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1952SuppLexicon"/><citedRange unit="page"> 2</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> <sense n="L" xml:id="TL"><foreign xml:lang="gez">ሃሌታ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>hālletā</quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>the chanting of hallelujah</quote></cit>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1952SuppLexicon"/><citedRange unit="page"> 2</citedRange></bibl> collection of various modes of singing hallelujah; <lb/>
 (<foreign xml:lang="gez">አንቀጸ፡ ሃሌታ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>ʾanqaṣa hālletā</quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>index of types of melodies</quote></cit>) <bibl><ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/><citedRange unit="page"> 217</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> </sense></entry>
